This is a small tool for building an application with a minimal
amount of red tape.

Usage:

  build appname

How it works:

  1) open appname.c
  2) look for the key lines in appname.c
  3) look for key lines in dependencies of appname.c
  4) compile everything

How to add to your app:

//LIBS ...

Specify the linker arguments.
Example:

  //LIBS -lncurses


//USES

Specify dependencies.
Example:

  //USES a b c d

a, b, c, and d will be built and linked against appname


//FLAGS

Specify custom compiler flags.
Example:

  //FLAGS -Wall -O3


All of these lines must start in the first column of the code;
indentions will be ignored silently.
